<img src="http://feeds2.feedburner.com/~r/eimaj/~4/rweZB80lf2Q" height="1" width="1"/>";s:14:"date_timestamp";i:1238471046;}i:1;a:14:{s:5:"title";s:9:"Rock Band";s:4:"link";s:52:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/eimaj/~3/UkZ1DL3NfFo/";s:8:"comments";s:36:"http://eimaj.net/rock-band/#comments";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Fri, 06 Mar 2009 02:00:32 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:5:"jamie";}s:8:"category";s:44:"Day to DayFort ErieGuitar HeromusicRock Band";s:4:"guid";s:23:"http://eimaj.net/?p=190";s:11:"description";s:307:"Last weekend I went to Fort Erie to participate in the Bowl for Kids Sake campaign. We raised a ton of money and once I get a few more details I&#8217;ll write a post about how awesome we are. &#8220;We&#8221; includes Zoë, James and Todd.
But following bowling &#8212; as well as a bit before &#8212; [...]";s:7:"content";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";s:1921:"<p>Last weekend I went to Fort Erie to participate in the <a href="http://www.bigbrothersbigsisters.ca/forterie/en/Home/Sponsorship/bowlforkids.aspx">Bowl for Kids Sake</a> campaign. We raised a ton of money and once I get a few more details I&#8217;ll write a post about how awesome we are. &#8220;We&#8221; includes <a title="The Medium and the Message" href="http://www.mediumandthemessage.com/" target="_blank">Zoë</a>, James and <a title="Digital Todd" href="http://blog.pc-geektech.com/" target="_blank">Todd</a>.</p>
<p>But following bowling &#8212; as well as a bit before &#8212; we were hanging out at Todd&#8217;s parents house. While there Rock Band was played. I&#8217;m not a huge fan of the game because of my not-so-sound-proof floor and my ex-let&#8217;s-play-rock-band-after-the-bar-on-a-weeknight neighbours. But I&#8217;m also not very good at it. Last weekend I figured out why.</p>
<div align="center"><a href="http://imgs.xkcd.com/comics/rock_band.png"><img title="Rock Band" src="http://imgs.xkcd.com/comics/rock_band.png" alt="photo from xkcd.com" width="404" height="212" /></a></div>
<p><span id="more-190"></span>For me music is an audio and kinetic thing. I can play a few instruments and when I play I pick things up by ear and interpret them into chords I can play. With Rock Band, and it&#8217;s cousin Guitar Hero, the cues you look for from the game aren&#8217;t audio, they&#8217;re visual. On top of that, the audio doesn&#8217;t always match up with what you are supposed to play in order to not suck. Hence my lack of skills.</p>
<p>But I had a lot of fun anyways. I also secretly recorded people playing. I&#8217;m not going to out any of the players, but I will say that I may have mentioned some of them already in this post. Enjoy!</p>
<div align="center" style="margin-bottom:16px;">

</div>
