<img src="http://feeds2.feedburner.com/~r/eimaj/~4/jpQwfo_eU10" height="1" width="1"/>";s:14:"date_timestamp";i:1235705558;}i:3;a:14:{s:5:"title";s:31:"There?s no fighting the weather";s:4:"link";s:52:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/eimaj/~3/R1-C_Pn8xnc/";s:8:"comments";s:57:"http://eimaj.net/theres-no-fighting-the-weather/#comments";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Wed, 04 Feb 2009 01:29:00 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:5:"jamie";}s:8:"category";s:14:"Day to Daysnow";s:4:"guid";s:22:"http://eimaj.net/?p=93";s:11:"description";s:309:"I don?t know if I?m just living a very sheltered existence, but I?m not feeling all that phased by all the snow. Sure it?s slightly inconvenient, but we do live in Canada. It?s kind of expected.
So far this year, there have been a pile of cancellations, snow days, all kinds of terrible drivers and some [...]";s:7:"content";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";s:2294:"<p><img class="alignright" style="float: right;" src="http://eimaj.net/wp-content/uploads/2009/02/snow_walk.jpg" alt="a night walk" width="220" height="166" />I don?t know if I?m just living a very sheltered existence, but I?m not feeling all that phased by all the snow. Sure it?s slightly inconvenient, but we do live in Canada. It?s kind of expected.</p>
<p>So far this year, there have been a pile of cancellations, snow days, all kinds of terrible drivers and some pretty spectacular accidents, but I?m feeling pretty good about the snow.</p>
<p>The key to surviving and enjoying this weather is slowing down. The pace at which people seem to need to move from place to place can?t be maintained when there is piles of fluffy frozen water on the ground. It?s just not safe.</p>
<p>While I was thinking of all this and clearing off my car I compiled a small list of fun things I like to do in the snow.<span id="more-93"></span></p>
<p><strong>Go for a walk in the middle of the night</strong></p>
<blockquote><p>There is nothing more serene that a sleeping snow-filled city/town/village/street. I?ve tried taking photos (above), but they never quite capture the moment.</p></blockquote>
<p><strong>Build a quinzhee</strong></p>
<blockquote><p>A <a title="how to build a quinzhee" href="http://www.ottawaoutdoors.ca/index.php?option=com_content&amp;task=view&amp;id=118" target="_blank">pile of snow you can sleep in</a>. What could be more fun?</p></blockquote>
<p><strong>Make snow creations</strong></p>
<blockquote><p>Calvin had it right. Scare you neighbours, express yourself or just be weird.</p></blockquote>
<p><img src="http://www.chase3000.com/userpages/calvinhobbes/Evolution.gif" alt="Some Calvin snow creations" width="480" height="160" /></p>
<p><strong>Ski, snowshoe or slide on it</strong></p>
<blockquote><p>There are all kinds of outdoor sports you can participate and you don?t even have to leave your neighbourhood.</p></blockquote>
<p><strong>Throw it</strong></p>
<blockquote><p>Not sure there is anything more fun that a good old-fashioned snow-throw.</p></blockquote>
<p><img src="http://www.geocities.com/hoffler_b/real_friend.JPG" alt="The perfect snowball" width="480" /></p>
