<p>So far this year, there have been a pile of cancellations, snow days, all kinds of terrible drivers and some pretty spectacular accidents, but I?m feeling pretty good about the snow.</p>
<p>The key to surviving and enjoying this weather is slowing down. The pace at which people seem to need to move from place to place can?t be maintained when there is piles of fluffy frozen water on the ground. It?s just not safe.</p>
<p>While I was thinking of all this and clearing off my car I compiled a small list of fun things I like to do in the snow.<span id="more-93"></span></p>
<p><strong>Go for a walk in the middle of the night</strong></p>
<blockquote><p>There is nothing more serene that a sleeping snow-filled city/town/village/street. I?ve tried taking photos (above), but they never quite capture the moment.</p></blockquote>
<p><strong>Build a quinzhee</strong></p>
<blockquote><p>A <a title="how to build a quinzhee" href="http://www.ottawaoutdoors.ca/index.php?option=com_content&amp;task=view&amp;id=118" target="_blank">pile of snow you can sleep in</a>. What could be more fun?</p></blockquote>
