<img src="http://feeds2.feedburner.com/~r/eimaj/~4/R1-C_Pn8xnc" height="1" width="1"/>";s:14:"date_timestamp";i:1233710940;}i:4;a:14:{s:5:"title";s:19:"Twitter Backgrounds";s:4:"link";s:52:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/eimaj/~3/kUfhvATCDyc/";s:8:"comments";s:46:"http://eimaj.net/twitter-backgrounds/#comments";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Sat, 31 Jan 2009 02:28:37 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:5:"jamie";}s:8:"category";s:26:"PortfoliodesignfordTwitter";s:4:"guid";s:23:"http://eimaj.net/?p=169";s:11:"description";s:119:"Twitter backgrounds for Ford on behalf of <a href="http://socialmediagroup.com" target="_blank">Social Media Group</a>.";s:7:"content";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";s:1799:"<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="tt-flickr tt-flickr-Medium" href="http://twitter.com/FordCustService"><img style="border: 0pt none;" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3660/3308408602_d27a54861b.jpg" border="0" alt="@FordCustService" width="282" height="151" /></a> <a class="tt-flickr tt-flickr-Medium" href="http://twitter.com/FordDriveOne"><img class="aligncenter" style="border: 0pt none;" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3338/3307577305_2be7acc03d.jpg" border="0" alt="@FordDriveOne" width="282" height="165" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Working at <a title="Social Media Group" href="http://socialmediagroup.com/" target="_blank">Social Media Group</a> (SMG) has provided me with the opportunity to work with some big clients on behalf of SMG.</p>
<p>At SMG we helped Ford develop a Twitter strategy and set up several Twitter accounts for them.  I designed the backgrounds for two of these accounts: <a title="@FordDriveOne" href="http://twitter.com/FordDriveOne" target="_blank">@FordDriveOne</a> and <a title="@FordCustService" href="http://twitter.com/FordCustService" target="_blank">@FordCustService</a>.</p>
<p>They are also featured on <a title="twitterbackgroundsgallery.com" href="http://twitterbackgroundsgallery.com/category/big-brands/" target="_blank">Twitter Backgrounds Gallery</a>. You can check them out and vote for them here: <a title="@FordDriveOne on twitterbackgroundsgallery.com" href="http://twitterbackgroundsgallery.com/2009/01/28/forddriveone/" target="_blank">@FordDriveOne</a> and <a title="@FordDriveOne on twitterbackgroundsgallery.com" href="http://twitterbackgroundsgallery.com/2009/01/23/fordcustservice/" target="_blank">@FordCustService</a></p>
<img src="http://feeds2.feedburner.com/~r/eimaj/~4/kUfhvATCDyc" height="1" width="1"/>";}s:3:"wfw";a:1:{s:10:"commentrss";s:42:"http://eimaj.net/twitter-backgrounds/feed/";}s:10:"feedburner";a:1:{s:8:"origlink";s:37:"http://eimaj.net/twitter-backgrounds/";}s:7:"summary";s:119:"Twitter backgrounds for Ford on behalf of <a href="http://socialmediagroup.com" target="_blank">Social Media Group</a>.";s:12:"atom_content";s:1799:"<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="tt-flickr tt-flickr-Medium" href="http://twitter.com/FordCustService"><img style="border: 0pt none;" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3660/3308408602_d27a54861b.jpg" border="0" alt="@FordCustService" width="282" height="151" /></a> <a class="tt-flickr tt-flickr-Medium" href="http://twitter.com/FordDriveOne"><img class="aligncenter" style="border: 0pt none;" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3338/3307577305_2be7acc03d.jpg" border="0" alt="@FordDriveOne" width="282" height="165" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Working at <a title="Social Media Group" href="http://socialmediagroup.com/" target="_blank">Social Media Group</a> (SMG) has provided me with the opportunity to work with some big clients on behalf of SMG.</p>
<p>At SMG we helped Ford develop a Twitter strategy and set up several Twitter accounts for them.  I designed the backgrounds for two of these accounts: <a title="@FordDriveOne" href="http://twitter.com/FordDriveOne" target="_blank">@FordDriveOne</a> and <a title="@FordCustService" href="http://twitter.com/FordCustService" target="_blank">@FordCustService</a>.</p>
<p>They are also featured on <a title="twitterbackgroundsgallery.com" href="http://twitterbackgroundsgallery.com/category/big-brands/" target="_blank">Twitter Backgrounds Gallery</a>. You can check them out and vote for them here: <a title="@FordDriveOne on twitterbackgroundsgallery.com" href="http://twitterbackgroundsgallery.com/2009/01/28/forddriveone/" target="_blank">@FordDriveOne</a> and <a title="@FordDriveOne on twitterbackgroundsgallery.com" href="http://twitterbackgroundsgallery.com/2009/01/23/fordcustservice/" target="_blank">@FordCustService</a></p>
<img src="http://feeds2.feedburner.com/~r/eimaj/~4/kUfhvATCDyc" height="1" width="1"/>";s:14:"date_timestamp";i:1233368917;}i:5;a:14:{s:5:"title";s:15:"Thomas K. Allen";s:4:"link";s:52:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/eimaj/~3/Er9dpmpSvV8/";s:8:"comments";s:41:"http://eimaj.net/thomas-k-allen/#comments";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Thu, 22 Jan 2009 23:52:40 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:5:"jamie";}s:8:"category";s:23:"Day to Dayeulogygrandpa";s:4:"guid";s:22:"http://eimaj.net/?p=92";s:11:"description";s:321:"
Sorry I&#8217;ve been a bit MIA for the past.. uh.. two months. Things have been a little crazy. The holidays in particular were a very busy time and things are just starting to settle back into a somewhat irregular rhythm.
I&#8217;m going to try to get back into regular updates, but I&#8217;m starting with a sad [...]";s:7:"content";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";s:2976:"<p><a href="http://eimaj.net/wp-content/uploads/2009/01/grandpa.jpg"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-80" title="The pillowcase." src="http://eimaj.net/wp-content/uploads/2009/01/grandpa.jpg" alt="Grandpa, Christmas 2007" width="247" /></a></p>
<p>Sorry I&#8217;ve been a bit MIA for the past.. uh.. two months. Things have been a little crazy. The holidays in particular were a very busy time and things are just starting to settle back into a somewhat irregular rhythm.</p>
<p>I&#8217;m going to try to get back into regular updates, but I&#8217;m starting with a sad one.</p>
<p>My grandfather passed away on January 9th, 2009 at the ripe old age of 92. He was an enormous part of our lives and he will be dearly missed. He lived a full and very busy life and it was clear by the number of people at the funeral service that he had a very huge impact on everyone he met.</p>
<p>I spoke during the service along with my cousin, my dad and one of Grandpa&#8217;s good friends. It was a beautiful service and I want to say again how much we all appreciated the support and kind words.</p>
<p>Here is what I said at the service:</p>
<blockquote><p>Last year I went to the <a href="http://eimaj.net/how-to-be-immortal/">Remembrance Day ceremony at the Swansea Memorial Library</a> in Toronto. At the service my great grandfather, Arthur Thomas Allen, was remembered for his service in WWI. The Swansea Historical Foundation dedicated a giant hand-painted mural to him and 21 other fallen soldiers from Swansea. Each soldier was also remembered through a plaque.</p>
<p>Grandpa was there and there were also a number of the boys from his old scout troop. The ceremony and seeing Grandpa talking with his old Scouts got me thinking about being remembered and living beyond your time.</p>
<p>Throughout Grandpa&#8217;s lifetime he inspired and led a number of people and organizations. I don&#8217;t doubt that he left an impression on every one of them. Many of the people who have met him, refer to him as one of the people who inspired, motivated and influenced them.</p>
<p>Everyone here probably has a story or two about him. I know his family could talk for hours about some of the games we played or the antics that would invariably happen at fancy restaurants. We could probably re-tell most of his stories and jokes almost as well as he could.</p>
<p>Grandpa&#8217;s story is ours now. Through our telling of it he will live forever.</p>
<p>The other night while I was writing this I was reminded of the movie, <a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0319061/" target="_blank"><em>Big Fish</em></a>. So I watched it. I&#8217;d like to end with a quote from it that I think sums up what I&#8217;m trying to say:</p>
<p>&#8220;A man tells his stories so many times, that he becomes his stories. They live on after him. And in that way he becomes immortal.&#8221;</p></blockquote>
<img src="http://feeds2.feedburner.com/~r/eimaj/~4/Er9dpmpSvV8" height="1" width="1"/>";}s:3:"wfw";a:1:{s:10:"commentrss";s:37:"http://eimaj.net/thomas-k-allen/feed/";}s:10:"feedburner";a:1:{s:8:"origlink";s:32:"http://eimaj.net/thomas-k-allen/";}s:7:"summary";s:321:"
Sorry I&#8217;ve been a bit MIA for the past.. uh.. two months. Things have been a little crazy. The holidays in particular were a very busy time and things are just starting to settle back into a somewhat irregular rhythm.
I&#8217;m going to try to get back into regular updates, but I&#8217;m starting with a sad [...]";s:12:"atom_content";s:2976:"<p><a href="http://eimaj.net/wp-content/uploads/2009/01/grandpa.jpg"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-80" title="The pillowcase." src="http://eimaj.net/wp-content/uploads/2009/01/grandpa.jpg" alt="Grandpa, Christmas 2007" width="247" /></a></p>
<p>Sorry I&#8217;ve been a bit MIA for the past.. uh.. two months. Things have been a little crazy. The holidays in particular were a very busy time and things are just starting to settle back into a somewhat irregular rhythm.</p>
<p>I&#8217;m going to try to get back into regular updates, but I&#8217;m starting with a sad one.</p>
<p>My grandfather passed away on January 9th, 2009 at the ripe old age of 92. He was an enormous part of our lives and he will be dearly missed. He lived a full and very busy life and it was clear by the number of people at the funeral service that he had a very huge impact on everyone he met.</p>
<p>I spoke during the service along with my cousin, my dad and one of Grandpa&#8217;s good friends. It was a beautiful service and I want to say again how much we all appreciated the support and kind words.</p>
<p>Here is what I said at the service:</p>
<blockquote><p>Last year I went to the <a href="http://eimaj.net/how-to-be-immortal/">Remembrance Day ceremony at the Swansea Memorial Library</a> in Toronto. At the service my great grandfather, Arthur Thomas Allen, was remembered for his service in WWI. The Swansea Historical Foundation dedicated a giant hand-painted mural to him and 21 other fallen soldiers from Swansea. Each soldier was also remembered through a plaque.</p>
<p>Grandpa was there and there were also a number of the boys from his old scout troop. The ceremony and seeing Grandpa talking with his old Scouts got me thinking about being remembered and living beyond your time.</p>
<p>Throughout Grandpa&#8217;s lifetime he inspired and led a number of people and organizations. I don&#8217;t doubt that he left an impression on every one of them. Many of the people who have met him, refer to him as one of the people who inspired, motivated and influenced them.</p>
<p>Everyone here probably has a story or two about him. I know his family could talk for hours about some of the games we played or the antics that would invariably happen at fancy restaurants. We could probably re-tell most of his stories and jokes almost as well as he could.</p>
<p>Grandpa&#8217;s story is ours now. Through our telling of it he will live forever.</p>
<p>The other night while I was writing this I was reminded of the movie, <a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0319061/" target="_blank"><em>Big Fish</em></a>. So I watched it. I&#8217;d like to end with a quote from it that I think sums up what I&#8217;m trying to say:</p>
<p>&#8220;A man tells his stories so many times, that he becomes his stories. They live on after him. And in that way he becomes immortal.&#8221;</p></blockquote>
<img src="http://feeds2.feedburner.com/~r/eimaj/~4/Er9dpmpSvV8" height="1" width="1"/>";s:14:"date_timestamp";i:1232668360;}i:6;a:14:{s:5:"title";s:18:"How to be immortal";s:4:"link";s:52:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/eimaj/~3/t_tqKVSeCJA/";s:8:"comments";s:45:"http://eimaj.net/how-to-be-immortal/#comments";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Wed, 19 Nov 2008 01:28:49 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:5:"jamie";}s:8:"category";s:63:"Day to Dayimmortalmuralrememberance daySwansea Memorial Library";s:4:"guid";s:22:"http://eimaj.net/?p=91";s:11:"description";s:338:"Last week I went to a remembrance day ceremony in Toronto. My great grandfather and twenty-one other soldiers were being remembered for their service in WWI with a giant mural at the Swansea Memorial Library. Arthur Thomas Allen was a bombadier who never came home. My grandfather never met his dad.
The mural was revealed following [...]";s:7:"content";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";s:2824:"<p>Last week I went to a remembrance day ceremony in Toronto. My great grandfather and twenty-one other soldiers were being remembered for their service in WWI with a giant mural at the Swansea Memorial Library. Arthur Thomas Allen was a bombadier who never came home. My grandfather never met his dad.</p>
<p>The mural was revealed following the service.  It depicted the history of the area and included a plaque for each of the twenty-two soldiers from the area who never came home, including my great grandfather.</p>
<p><img class="alignright" style="float: right;" title="L to R: Eileen Allen aka Grandma, Joyce Jennison, Tom Allen aka Grandpa" src="http://eimaj.net/wp-content/uploads/2008/11/remember.jpg" alt="L to R: Eileen Allen aka Grandma, Joyce Jennison, Tom Allen aka Grandpa" width="200" />My grandfather, Thomas Allen (the third), is now 92. During his life he has inspired and led a number of organizations from Scouts to Kiwanis to Ontario Hydro.  He?s been married to my grandmother, Eileen, for 64 years and they?re still going strong.</p>
<p>At the service there were a few of the old boys from his scout troop and it was great to watch them talk and reminisce. The thing I found most interesting was to see what these boys had done with their lives. <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/David_Crombie" target="_blank">David Crombie</a> was the Mayor of Toronto, a federal MP and is still active in the political community. Norman McLeod led the creation of the Swansea WWI memorial mural and is a prominent member of the <a href="http://www.swanseatownhall.ca/" target="_blank">Swansea Community</a>. Bill Tennison is still a Scout leader himself after more than 60 years in scouting. All are still very active in the community and regard my grandfather as the one of the people in their lives who inspired and influenced them.</p>
<p>I think this is one of my grandfather&#8217;s legacies. He has and still does inspire, motivate and entertain everyone he meets and every one of those people will always remember him for it.</p>
<p>This got me thinking. Is there anyone who I?ve encountered in my life who are now doing really huge things? Have my actions inspired them in any way? I can think of a few people and I think they know who they are. I?m really proud of the things they?re doing and I hope they keep it up. They?re changing the world.</p>
<p>To me this is what immortality is. Not the things that we collect and pass on to our survivors, not trying to physically live forever but the memories and the people that continue our lives beyond our physical lifespan. All those intangible, immeasurable things that are passed on through memory and story.</p>
<p>How about you? What will your legacy be?</p>
<img src="http://feeds2.feedburner.com/~r/eimaj/~4/t_tqKVSeCJA" height="1" width="1"/>";}s:3:"wfw";a:1:{s:10:"commentrss";s:41:"http://eimaj.net/how-to-be-immortal/feed/";}s:10:"feedburner";a:1:{s:8:"origlink";s:36:"http://eimaj.net/how-to-be-immortal/";}s:7:"summary";s:338:"Last week I went to a remembrance day ceremony in Toronto. My great grandfather and twenty-one other soldiers were being remembered for their service in WWI with a giant mural at the Swansea Memorial Library. Arthur Thomas Allen was a bombadier who never came home. My grandfather never met his dad.
